{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01HAQmRgAtAh7w5bY6i7w2kQ","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 11.1: Workflow Schema Extension\n2\t\n3\tStatus: verifying\n4\t\n5\t<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n6\t\n7\t## Story\n8\t\n9\tAs a user,\n10\tI want to specify `driver`, `model`, and `plugins` per task in my workflow YAML,\n11\tso that I can control which framework and model each task uses without modifying engine code.\n12\t\n13\t## Acceptance Criteria\n14\t\n15\t1. **Given** the workflow schema at `src/schemas/workflow.schema.json`\n16\t   **When** updated with `driver`, `model`, and `plugins` fields on the task definition\n17\t   **Then** the `driver` field is type `string`, optional, with no schema-level default (engine defaults to `claude-code` at dispatch time)\n18\t   **And** the `model` field is type `string`, optional, with no default (falls through to model resolution chain)\n19\t   **And** the `plugins` field is type `array` of `string`, optional\n20\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n21\t\n22\t2. **Given** an existing workflow YAML with no `driver`, `model`, or `plugins` fields on any task\n23\t   **When** the workflow is parsed and validated via `parseWorkflow()` or `resolveWorkflow()`\n24\t   **Then** it validates successfully with zero errors\n25\t   **And** the resolved tasks have `driver`, `model`, and `plugins` as `undefined`\n26\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n27\t\n28\t3. **Given** a workflow YAML with `driver: codex`, `model: codex-mini`, and `plugins: ['gstack']` on a task\n29\t   **When** parsed via `parseWorkflow()`\n30\t   **Then** the `ResolvedTask` for that task has `driver === 'codex'`, `model === 'codex-mini'`, and `plugins` as `['gstack']`\n31\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n32\t\n33\t4. **Given** the `ResolvedTask` interface in `src/lib/workflow-parser.ts`\n34\t   **When** inspected\n35\t   **Then** it includes optional `driver?: string`, `model?: string`, and `plugins?: string[]` fields\n36\t   **And** existing fields (`agent`, `scope`, `session`, `source_access`, etc.) remain unchanged\n37\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n38\t\n39\t5. **Given** the `validateAndResolve()` function in `workflow-parser.ts`\n40\t   **When** it processes tasks with the new fields\n41\t   **Then** it populates `driver`, `model`, and `plugins` on `ResolvedTask` from the parsed YAML\n42\t   **And** omits them (leaves as `undefined`) when not present in the source YAML\n43\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n44\t\n45\t6. **Given** the `additionalProperties: false` constraint on the task definition in the schema\n46\t   **When** a workflow YAML includes a task with only the new fields (`driver`, `model`, `plugins`) alongside `agent`\n47\t   **Then** schema validation passes (the new fields are recognized, not rejected as additional properties)\n48\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n49\t\n50\t7. **Given** `npm run build` is executed\n51\t   **When** the build completes\n52\t   **Then** it succeeds with zero TypeScript errors\n53\t   **And** `npm run test:unit` passes with no regressions in existing test suites\n54\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n55\t\n56\t8. **Given** unit tests for the schema extension\n57\t   **When** `npm run test:unit` is executed\n58\t   **Then** tests verify that tasks with `driver`, `model`, and `plugins` parse correctly\n59\t   **And** tests verify backward compatibility with existing workflows (no new fields present)\n60\t   **And** tests verify that invalid types for the new fields (e.g., `driver: 123`) are rejected by schema validation\n61\t   **And** tests verify the `ResolvedTask` type exposes the new optional fields\n62\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n63\t\n64\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n65\t\n66\t- [x] Task 1: Extend `workflow.schema.json` with new fields (AC: #1, #6)\n67\t  - [x] Add `driver` property: `{ \"type\": \"string\", \"description\": \"Agent driver framework (e.g., claude-code, codex, opencode)\" }` to task definition\n68\t  - [x] Add `model` property: `{ \"type\": \"string\", \"description\": \"Model override for this task (falls through to resolution chain if omitted)\" }` to task definition\n69\t  - [x] Add `plugins` property: `{ \"type\": \"array\", \"items\": { \"type\": \"string\" }, \"description\": \"Plugin names to load in the driver session\" }` to task definition\n70\t  - [x] Verify `additionalProperties: false` still works — new fields are in the schema so they won't be rejected\n71\t\n72\t- [x] Task 2: Extend `ResolvedTask` interface (AC: #4)\n73\t  - [x] Add `driver?: string` to `ResolvedTask`\n74\t  - [x] Add `model?: string` to `ResolvedTask`\n75\t  - [x] Add `plugins?: string[]` to `ResolvedTask`\n76\t\n77\t- [x] Task 3: Update `validateAndResolve()` to populate new fields (AC: #2, #3, #5)\n78\t  - [x] In the task resolution loop, add: `if (task.driver !== undefined) resolved.driver = task.driver as string;`\n79\t  - [x] Add: `if (task.model !== undefined) resolved.model = task.model as string;`\n80\t  - [x] Add: `if (task.plugins !== undefined) resolved.plugins = task.plugins as string[];`\n81\t  - [x] Do NOT set defaults for these fields — they remain `undefined` when absent\n82\t\n83\t- [x] Task 4: Write unit tests (AC: #7, #8)\n84\t  - [x] Test: minimal workflow (no new fields) parses successfully — backward compat\n85\t  - [x] Test: task with `driver: codex` parses into `ResolvedTask.driver === 'codex'`\n86\t  - [x] Test: task with `model: claude-opus-4` parses into `ResolvedTask.model === 'claude-opus-4'`\n87\t  - [x] Test: task with `plugins: ['gstack', 'omo']` parses into `ResolvedTask.plugins`\n88\t  - [x] Test: task with all three new fields parses correctly\n89\t  - [x] Test: `driver: 123` (wrong type) fails schema validation\n90\t  - [x] Test: `model: true` (wrong type) fails schema validation\n91\t  - [x] Test: `plugins: \"not-array\"` (wrong type) fails schema validation\n92\t  - [x] Verify `npm run build` succeeds with zero errors\n93\t  - [x] Verify `npm run test:unit` passes with no regressions\n94\t\n95\t- [x] Task 5: Remove forward-compat hacks in `workflow-engine.ts` (AC: #4)\n96\t  - [x] Replace `(task as { driver?: string }).driver` with `task.driver` (now a real field)\n97\t  - [x] Replace `(task as { plugins?: readonly string[] }).plugins` with `task.plugins`\n98\t  - [x] Verify TypeScript compiles without errors after this cleanup\n99\t\n100\t## Dev Notes\n101\t\n102\t### Architecture Compliance\n103\t\n104\tThis story implements Epic 2, Story 2.1 \"Workflow Schema Extension\" from `epics-multi-framework.md`. It covers FR11 (per-task driver field), FR12 (per-task model field), and partially FR15 (backward compatibility for existing workflows).\n105\t\n106\tKey architecture decisions honored:\n107\t- **Decision 1 (Driver Interface):** `driver` field names match `AgentDriver.name` values registered in the factory\n108\t- **Decision 4 (Model Resolution):** `model` field is optional — absence means \"fall through to model resolution chain\" (`resolveModel(task, agent, driver)` in `model-resolver.ts`)\n109\t- **Decision 6 (Plugin Pass-Through):** `plugins` array is a list of plugin names, translated by drivers to framework-specific CLI flags\n110\t\n111\t### Current State of the Codebase\n112\t\n113\t- **`workflow.schema.json`** has `additionalProperties: false` on the task definition. New fields MUST be added to the schema or they will be rejected as unknown properties.\n114\t- **`ResolvedTask`** in `workflow-parser.ts` currently has: `agent`, `scope`, `session`, `source_access`, `prompt_template?`, `input_contract?`, `output_contract?`, `max_budget_usd?`. No `driver`, `model`, or `plugins` fields.\n115\t- **`validateAndResolve()`** in `workflow-parser.ts` builds `ResolvedTask` objects from parsed YAML. It applies defaults for `scope`, `session`, and `source_access`. The new fields should NOT have defaults — they are purely optional.\n116\t- **`workflow-engine.ts`** currently uses `(task as { driver?: string }).driver ?? 'claude-code'` as a forward-compat hack from story 10-5. Once `ResolvedTask` has the `driver` field, this cast can be replaced with `task.driver ?? 'claude-code'`.\n117\t- **`schema-validate.ts`** compiles the JSON schema via Ajv. Changes to `workflow.schema.json` are automatically picked up — no code change needed in the validator.\n118\t- **Existing tests** in `workflow-parser.test.ts` test minimal and full YAML parsing. New tests should follow the same patterns (write YAML to temp dir, call `parseWorkflow()`, assert on `ResolvedTask` fields).\n119\t\n120\t### What NOT to Do\n121\t\n122\t- Do NOT add referential integrity checks for `driver` values (that's story 11-2)\n123\t- Do NOT add referential integrity checks for `agent` values against agent templates (that's story 11-2)\n124\t- Do NOT modify `model-resolver.ts` — it already handles the resolution chain\n125\t- Do NOT modify `factory.ts` or any driver files\n126\t- Do NOT add defaults for `driver` or `model` in the schema or parser — the engine handles defaults at dispatch time\n127\t- Do NOT modify the `flow` section schema — only `task` definitions change\n128\t\n129\t### Previous Story Intelligence\n130\t\n131\tFrom story 10-5 (Workflow Engine Driver Integration):\n132\t- The engine already uses `(task as { driver?: string }).driver ?? 'claude-code'` — this is the forward-compat pattern that this story makes official\n133\t- The engine passes `(task as { plugins?: readonly string[] }).plugins` to `DispatchOpts` — same pattern\n134\t- `DispatchError` import from `agent-dispatch.ts` was kept for backward compat\n135\t- 108 tests in workflow-engine.test.ts, 4321 tests total across 164 files\n136\t\n137\t### File Structure\n138\t\n139\tFiles to modify:\n140\t- `src/schemas/workflow.schema.json` — add `driver`, `model`, `plugins` to task definition\n141\t- `src/lib/workflow-parser.ts` — extend `ResolvedTask` interface and `validateAndResolve()` \n142\t- `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` — remove forward-compat type casts (cleanup)\n143\t- `src/lib/__tests__/workflow-parser.test.ts` — new test cases for the extended schema\n144\t\n145\tFiles NOT to modify:\n146\t- `src/lib/schema-validate.ts` — auto-picks up schema changes\n147\t- `src/lib/agents/drivers/factory.ts` — unchanged\n148\t- `src/lib/agents/model-resolver.ts` — unchanged\n149\t- `src/lib/agents/types.ts` — unchanged\n150\t\n151\t### Testing Patterns\n152\t\n153\t- Follow existing patterns in `workflow-parser.test.ts`: write YAML to temp dir, call `parseWorkflow()`, assert on result\n154\t- Use `writeYaml()` helper already defined in the test file\n155\t- For schema validation failures, expect `WorkflowParseError` to be thrown\n156\t- Verify backward compatibility: all existing tests must continue to pass without modification\n157\t\n158\t### References\n159\t\n160\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-multi-framework.md#Story 2.1: Workflow Schema Extension]\n161\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-multi-framework.md#Decision 1: Driver Interface Design]\n162\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-multi-framework.md#Decision 4: Model Resolution]\n163\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-multi-framework.md#Decision 6: Plugin Ecosystem Pass-Through]\n164\t- [Source: src/schemas/workflow.schema.json — current task definition schema]\n165\t- [Source: src/lib/workflow-parser.ts — ResolvedTask interface, validateAndResolve()]\n166\t- [Source: src/lib/workflow-engine.ts — forward-compat type casts from story 10-5]\n167\t\n168\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n169\t## Verification Requirements\n170\t\n171\t- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/11-1-workflow-schema-extension-proof.md)\n172\t- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n173\t- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n174\t\n175\t## Documentation Requirements\n176\t\n177\t- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n178\t- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/11-1-workflow-schema-extension.md\n179\t\n180\t## Testing Requirements\n181\t\n182\t- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n183\t- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n184\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n185\t\n186\t## Dev Agent Record\n187\t\n188\t### Agent Model Used\n189\t\n190\t{{agent_model_name_version}}\n191\t\n192\t### Debug Log References\n193\t\n194\t### Completion Notes List\n195\t\n196\t### File List\n197\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01FmCyPivNsxxfc9yDSTFKdg","session_id":"4b1f7711-6ed7-4488-a0af-b261e761b450","uuid":"9f1b60e6-3935-4054-a5d8-0adaa6251815","timestamp":"2026-04-03T08:26:21.907Z"}
