{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Rtrz2a2vhL4QwhRAajDg6E","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 11.2: Workflow Referential Integrity Validation\n2\t\n3\tStatus: ready-for-dev\n4\t\n5\t<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n6\t\n7\t## Story\n8\t\n9\tAs a user,\n10\tI want the workflow parser to validate that all referenced drivers and agents exist,\n11\tso that I get clear errors before execution if my workflow configuration is wrong.\n12\t\n13\t## Acceptance Criteria\n14\t\n15\t1. **Given** a workflow YAML with `driver: codex` on a task\n16\t   **When** the workflow is parsed via `parseWorkflow()` or `resolveWorkflow()`\n17\t   **Then** the parser checks that `codex` is a registered driver name via the driver registry\n18\t   **And** if the driver is not registered, a `WorkflowParseError` is thrown listing the invalid driver name, the task name, and the set of registered drivers as a suggested fix\n19\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n20\t\n21\t2. **Given** a workflow YAML with `agent: dev` on a task\n22\t   **When** the workflow is parsed via `parseWorkflow()` or `resolveWorkflow()`\n23\t   **Then** the parser checks that `dev` exists as an embedded agent template (file `templates/agents/dev.yaml` exists)\n24\t   **And** if the agent template does not exist, a `WorkflowParseError` is thrown listing the invalid agent name, the task name, and available agent templates as a suggested fix\n25\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n26\t\n27\t3. **Given** a workflow YAML with multiple tasks, where one has `driver: nonexistent` and another has `agent: fake-agent`\n28\t   **When** the workflow is parsed\n29\t   **Then** all referential integrity errors are collected and reported in a single `WorkflowParseError` (not fail-fast on the first error)\n30\t   **And** each error includes the field name (`driver` or `agent`), the task name, and the invalid value\n31\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n32\t\n33\t4. **Given** a workflow YAML with `driver: claude-code` on a task (a valid registered driver)\n34\t   **When** the workflow is parsed\n35\t   **Then** validation passes without error for that task's driver field\n36\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n37\t\n38\t5. **Given** a workflow YAML where no tasks specify a `driver` field\n39\t   **When** the workflow is parsed\n40\t   **Then** validation passes (driver field is optional; the engine defaults to `claude-code` at dispatch time)\n41\t   **And** no referential integrity check is performed for absent driver fields\n42\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n43\t\n44\t6. **Given** a workflow YAML where a task specifies an agent that exists as a project-level or user-level override (not just embedded)\n45\t   **When** the workflow is parsed\n46\t   **Then** the agent validation accepts it if the agent can be resolved via `resolveAgent()` (embedded, user-level, or project-level)\n47\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n48\t\n49\t7. **Given** referential integrity validation\n50\t   **When** it runs\n51\t   **Then** it executes at parse time, after schema validation but before the `ResolvedWorkflow` is returned\n52\t   **And** the existing flow-to-task referential integrity check (dangling task refs in flow) still runs\n53\t   **And** both check types (flow refs + driver/agent refs) report errors in the same `WorkflowParseError` if both fail\n54\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n55\t\n56\t8. **Given** `npm run build` is executed after all changes\n57\t   **When** the build completes\n58\t   **Then** it succeeds with zero TypeScript errors\n59\t   **And** `npm run test:unit` passes with no regressions in existing test suites\n60\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n61\t\n62\t9. **Given** unit tests for the referential integrity validation\n63\t   **When** `npm run test:unit` is executed\n64\t   **Then** tests cover: valid driver passes, invalid driver fails with helpful error, valid agent passes, invalid agent fails with helpful error, multiple errors collected, absent driver/agent fields skip validation, backward compatibility with existing workflows\n65\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n66\t\n67\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n68\t\n69\t- [ ] Task 1: Add `listEmbeddedAgents()` utility to `agent-resolver.ts` (AC: #2, #6)\n70\t  - [ ] Add `export function listEmbeddedAgents(): string[]` that reads `templates/agents/` directory and returns agent names (filenames without `.yaml` extension)\n71\t  - [ ] This provides the \"available agents\" list for error messages without importing a hardcoded list\n72\t  - [ ] Consider also using `resolveAgent()` with try/catch for project-level overrides, or simply check filesystem existence\n73\t\n74\t- [ ] Task 2: Add `validateReferentialIntegrity()` function in `workflow-parser.ts` (AC: #1, #2, #3, #7)\n75\t  - [ ] Create a new internal function `validateReferentialIntegrity(data, taskNames)` called after schema validation and after the existing flow-ref check\n76\t  - [ ] For each task: if `driver` is defined, check `listDrivers()` from `factory.ts` — if not found, collect error `{ path: '/tasks/{name}/driver', message: 'Driver \"{value}\" not found. Registered drivers: {list}' }`\n77\t  - [ ] For each task: if `agent` is defined, try `resolveAgent(agent)` or check `listEmbeddedAgents()` — if not found, collect error `{ path: '/tasks/{name}/agent', message: 'Agent \"{value}\" not found. Available agents: {list}' }`\n78\t  - [ ] Combine all collected errors with any existing dangling-ref errors\n79\t  - [ ] Throw single `WorkflowParseError` if any errors exist\n80\t\n81\t- [ ] Task 3: Integrate validation into `validateAndResolve()` (AC: #4, #5, #7)\n82\t  - [ ] Call `validateReferentialIntegrity()` after the existing flow-ref block but before building resolved tasks\n83\t  - [ ] Merge dangling-ref errors and integrity errors into one error list before throwing\n84\t  - [ ] Ensure absent `driver`/`agent` fields are skipped (only validate if present)\n85\t\n86\t- [ ] Task 4: Handle driver registry initialization concern (AC: #1, #4)\n87\t  - [ ] The driver registry (`factory.ts`) is populated at runtime when drivers register themselves. At parse time, the registry may be empty if no drivers have been registered yet.\n88\t  - [ ] Option A: Accept that driver validation only works when the registry is populated (document this; `workflow-engine.ts` already registers drivers before calling parse)\n89\t  - [ ] Option B: Add a `listKnownDriverNames()` that returns a hardcoded list of known driver names for static validation\n90\t  - [ ] Recommendation: Option A — validate only when `listDrivers().length > 0`, skip driver check if registry is empty (parse can be called independently of engine startup)\n91\t\n92\t- [ ] Task 5: Write unit tests (AC: #8, #9)\n93\t  - [ ] Test: workflow with `driver: claude-code` and registered driver passes validation\n94\t  - [ ] Test: workflow with `driver: nonexistent` throws `WorkflowParseError` with driver name, task name, and registered drivers\n95\t  - [ ] Test: workflow with `agent: dev` (valid embedded agent) passes validation\n96\t  - [ ] Test: workflow with `agent: nonexistent-agent` throws `WorkflowParseError` with agent name, task name, and available agents\n97\t  - [ ] Test: workflow with multiple invalid refs collects all errors in one throw\n98\t  - [ ] Test: workflow with no `driver` field on any task passes (optional field)\n99\t  - [ ] Test: existing flow-ref checks still work (regression guard)\n100\t  - [ ] Test: backward compatibility — existing test workflows parse without errors\n101\t  - [ ] Follow existing test patterns: write YAML to temp dir, call `parseWorkflow()`, assert on result/errors\n102\t\n103\t## Dev Notes\n104\t\n105\t### Architecture Compliance\n106\t\n107\tThis story implements Epic 2 (mapped to sprint Epic 11), Story 2.2 \"Workflow Referential Integrity Validation\" from `epics-multi-framework.md`. It covers FR14 (workflow YAML referential integrity: all referenced drivers exist, all referenced agents exist).\n108\t\n109\tKey architecture decisions honored:\n110\t- **Decision 1 (Driver Interface):** `driver` field names match `AgentDriver.name` values registered in the factory. This story validates that contract at parse time.\n111\t- **Architecture Boundary:** The workflow parser boundary is extended to validate cross-module references (drivers via factory, agents via resolver) without importing driver internals.\n112\t\n113\t### Current State of the Codebase\n114\t\n115\t- **`workflow-parser.ts`** already has flow-to-task referential integrity checking (lines 73-103). The new validation follows the same pattern: collect errors, throw once.\n116\t- **`factory.ts`** exports `listDrivers(): string[]` which returns registered driver names. Currently only `claude-code` is registered (by `workflow-engine.ts` at startup). The registry may be empty at standalone parse time.\n117\t- **`agent-resolver.ts`** exports `loadEmbeddedAgent(name)` which throws `AgentResolveError` if the agent doesn't exist. No listing function exists yet — must be added.\n118\t- **Embedded agent templates** live in `templates/agents/`: `dev`, `qa`, `architect`, `pm`, `sm`, `analyst`, `ux-designer`, `tech-writer`, `evaluator`.\n119\t- **`ResolvedTask`** already includes optional `driver?: string` and `model?: string` and `plugins?: string[]` from story 11-1.\n120\t- **`WorkflowParseError`** already carries structured errors as `Array<{ path: string; message: string }>` — the new validation produces errors in the same format.\n121\t\n122\t### What NOT to Do\n123\t\n124\t- Do NOT validate `model` field values — model resolution happens at dispatch time via `model-resolver.ts` and depends on runtime context (driver defaults, agent configs)\n125\t- Do NOT validate `plugins` values — plugin availability depends on the driver and runtime environment\n126\t- Do NOT modify `factory.ts` or any driver files — only consume `listDrivers()`\n127\t- Do NOT modify the JSON schema — the schema validates structure, this story validates semantic references\n128\t- Do NOT make driver validation fail when the registry is empty — parse can be called independently of engine startup (test scenarios, CLI validation commands)\n129\t- Do NOT import driver classes directly — use the registry API only\n130\t\n131\t### Import Strategy\n132\t\n133\tThe `validateAndResolve()` function in `workflow-parser.ts` will need new imports:\n134\t- `import { listDrivers } from './agents/drivers/factory.js';` — for driver name validation\n135\t- A new `listEmbeddedAgents` function or `resolveAgent` from `./agent-resolver.js` — for agent name validation\n136\t\n137\tKeep imports minimal. Prefer checking file existence over loading/parsing full agent configs.\n138\t\n139\t### Error Message Format\n140\t\n141\tFollow the existing pattern from `factory.ts` `getDriver()`:\n142\t```\n143\tDriver 'codex' not found. Registered drivers: claude-code\n144\t```\n145\t\n146\tFor agents:\n147\t```\n148\tAgent 'fake-agent' not found in task 'implement'. Available agents: dev, qa, architect, pm, sm, analyst, ux-designer, tech-writer, evaluator\n149\t```\n150\t\n151\t### Previous Story Intelligence\n152\t\n153\tFrom story 11-1 (Workflow Schema Extension):\n154\t- `driver`, `model`, and `plugins` fields were added to both `workflow.schema.json` and `ResolvedTask` interface\n155\t- Forward-compat type casts in `workflow-engine.ts` were cleaned up\n156\t- The parser already populates `resolved.driver`, `resolved.model`, `resolved.plugins` from parsed YAML\n157\t- Story 11-1 explicitly deferred referential integrity to this story (11-2): \"Do NOT add referential integrity checks for `driver` values (that's story 11-2)\"\n158\t- Test patterns: write YAML to temp dir via `writeYaml()` helper, call `parseWorkflow()`, assert on `ResolvedTask` fields or expect `WorkflowParseError`\n159\t\n160\t### Git Intelligence\n161\t\n162\tRecent commits (all in current sprint):\n163\t- `a4bf7e6` — story 11-1: workflow schema extension (driver/model/plugins on tasks)\n164\t- `f128064` — story 10-5: workflow engine driver integration\n165\t- `3717741` — story 10-4: model resolution module\n166\t- `bd3f35d` — story 10-3: ClaudeCodeDriver extraction\n167\t- `48d0524` — story 10-2: driver factory & registry\n168\t\n169\tAll recent work is in the driver/workflow area. The codebase patterns are fresh and consistent.\n170\t\n171\t### Project Structure Notes\n172\t\n173\tFiles to modify:\n174\t- `src/lib/workflow-parser.ts` — add `validateReferentialIntegrity()`, integrate into `validateAndResolve()`\n175\t- `src/lib/agent-resolver.ts` — add `listEmbeddedAgents()` utility\n176\t- `src/lib/__tests__/workflow-parser.test.ts` — new test cases for referential integrity\n177\t\n178\tFiles NOT to modify:\n179\t- `src/lib/agents/drivers/factory.ts` — consume only, don't change\n180\t- `src/schemas/workflow.schema.json` — schema validates structure, not semantic refs\n181\t- `src/lib/agents/drivers/types.ts` — unchanged\n182\t- `src/lib/agents/model-resolver.ts` — unchanged\n183\t- `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` — unchanged (it registers drivers before parsing)\n184\t\n185\t### Testing Patterns\n186\t\n187\t- Follow existing patterns in `workflow-parser.test.ts`: write YAML to temp dir, call `parseWorkflow()`, assert on result\n188\t- Use existing `writeYaml()` helper\n189\t- For validation failures, expect `WorkflowParseError` to be thrown with specific error messages\n190\t- For driver registry tests: call `registerDriver()` with mock drivers before parsing, call `resetDrivers()` in afterEach\n191\t- For agent tests: rely on embedded templates existing at known paths (they do in test environment)\n192\t- Verify backward compatibility: all existing tests must continue to pass\n193\t\n194\t### References\n195\t\n196\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-multi-framework.md#Story 2.2: Workflow Referential Integrity Validation]\n197\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-multi-framework.md#Decision 1: Driver Interface Design]\n198\t- [Source: src/lib/workflow-parser.ts — validateAndResolve(), existing flow-ref integrity check]\n199\t- [Source: src/lib/agents/drivers/factory.ts — listDrivers(), getDriver()]\n200\t- [Source: src/lib/agent-resolver.ts — loadEmbeddedAgent(), TEMPLATES_DIR]\n201\t- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/11-1-workflow-schema-extension.md — previous story context]\n202\t\n203\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n204\t## Verification Requirements\n205\t\n206\t- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/11-2-workflow-referential-integrity-validation-proof.md)\n207\t- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n208\t- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n209\t\n210\t## Documentation Requirements\n211\t\n212\t- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n213\t- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/11-2-workflow-referential-integrity-validation.md\n214\t\n215\t## Testing Requirements\n216\t\n217\t- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n218\t- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n219\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n220\t\n221\t## Dev Agent Record\n222\t\n223\t### Agent Model Used\n224\t\n225\t{{agent_model_name_version}}\n226\t\n227\t### Debug Log References\n228\t\n229\t### Completion Notes List\n230\t\n231\t### File List\n232\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01K9WPLAQDFLLNWtkamPogoK","session_id":"4b1f7711-6ed7-4488-a0af-b261e761b450","uuid":"8a61a1cb-e844-41d3-8c07-3b7ce8251b21","timestamp":"2026-04-03T08:30:06.697Z"}
