{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_012C16hgX6cU1bYmvtS6vBtm","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_017kRGLZwMLAD88YPjF3E2Vv","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/11-2-workflow-referential-integrity-validation.md","old_string":"- [ ] Task 1: Add `listEmbeddedAgents()` utility to `agent-resolver.ts` (AC: #2, #6)\n  - [ ] Add `export function listEmbeddedAgents(): string[]` that reads `templates/agents/` directory and returns agent names (filenames without `.yaml` extension)\n  - [ ] This provides the \"available agents\" list for error messages without importing a hardcoded list\n  - [ ] Consider also using `resolveAgent()` with try/catch for project-level overrides, or simply check filesystem existence\n\n- [ ] Task 2: Add `validateReferentialIntegrity()` function in `workflow-parser.ts` (AC: #1, #2, #3, #7)\n  - [ ] Create a new internal function `validateReferentialIntegrity(data, taskNames)` called after schema validation and after the existing flow-ref check\n  - [ ] For each task: if `driver` is defined, check `listDrivers()` from `factory.ts` — if not found, collect error `{ path: '/tasks/{name}/driver', message: 'Driver \"{value}\" not found. Registered drivers: {list}' }`\n  - [ ] For each task: if `agent` is defined, try `resolveAgent(agent)` or check `listEmbeddedAgents()` — if not found, collect error `{ path: '/tasks/{name}/agent', message: 'Agent \"{value}\" not found. Available agents: {list}' }`\n  - [ ] Combine all collected errors with any existing dangling-ref errors\n  - [ ] Throw single `WorkflowParseError` if any errors exist\n\n- [ ] Task 3: Integrate validation into `validateAndResolve()` (AC: #4, #5, #7)\n  - [ ] Call `validateReferentialIntegrity()` after the existing flow-ref block but before building resolved tasks\n  - [ ] Merge dangling-ref errors and integrity errors into one error list before throwing\n  - [ ] Ensure absent `driver`/`agent` fields are skipped (only validate if present)\n\n- [ ] Task 4: Handle driver registry initialization concern (AC: #1, #4)\n  - [ ] The driver registry (`factory.ts`) is populated at runtime when drivers register themselves. At parse time, the registry may be empty if no drivers have been registered yet.\n  - [ ] Option A: Accept that driver validation only works when the registry is populated (document this; `workflow-engine.ts` already registers drivers before calling parse)\n  - [ ] Option B: Add a `listKnownDriverNames()` that returns a hardcoded list of known driver names for static validation\n  - [ ] Recommendation: Option A — validate only when `listDrivers().length > 0`, skip driver check if registry is empty (parse can be called independently of engine startup)\n\n- [ ] Task 5: Write unit tests (AC: #8, #9)\n  - [ ] Test: workflow with `driver: claude-code` and registered driver passes validation\n  - [ ] Test: workflow with `driver: nonexistent` throws `WorkflowParseError` with driver name, task name, and registered drivers\n  - [ ] Test: workflow with `agent: dev` (valid embedded agent) passes validation\n  - [ ] Test: workflow with `agent: nonexistent-agent` throws `WorkflowParseError` with agent name, task name, and available agents\n  - [ ] Test: workflow with multiple invalid refs collects all errors in one throw\n  - [ ] Test: workflow with no `driver` field on any task passes (optional field)\n  - [ ] Test: existing flow-ref checks still work (regression guard)\n  - [ ] Test: backward compatibility — existing test workflows parse without errors\n  - [ ] Follow existing test patterns: write YAML to temp dir, call `parseWorkflow()`, assert on result/errors","new_string":"- [x] Task 1: Add `listEmbeddedAgents()` utility to `agent-resolver.ts` (AC: #2, #6)\n  - [x] Add `export function listEmbeddedAgents(): string[]` that reads `templates/agents/` directory and returns agent names (filenames without `.yaml` extension)\n  - [x] This provides the \"available agents\" list for error messages without importing a hardcoded list\n  - [x] Uses `readdirSync` on TEMPLATES_DIR, filters .yaml files, returns sorted names. Falls back to empty array on error.\n\n- [x] Task 2: Add `validateReferentialIntegrity()` function in `workflow-parser.ts` (AC: #1, #2, #3, #7)\n  - [x] Create a new internal function `validateReferentialIntegrity(data, taskNames, errors)` called after schema validation and after the existing flow-ref check\n  - [x] For each task: if `driver` is defined and registry is populated, check `listDrivers()` from `factory.ts` — if not found, collect error\n  - [x] For each task: if `agent` is defined, try `resolveAgent(agent)` — if not found, collect error with available agents list\n  - [x] Combine all collected errors with any existing dangling-ref errors\n  - [x] Throw single `WorkflowParseError` if any errors exist\n\n- [x] Task 3: Integrate validation into `validateAndResolve()` (AC: #4, #5, #7)\n  - [x] Call `validateReferentialIntegrity()` after the existing flow-ref block but before building resolved tasks\n  - [x] Merge dangling-ref errors and integrity errors into one error list before throwing\n  - [x] Ensure absent `driver`/`agent` fields are skipped (only validate if present)\n\n- [x] Task 4: Handle driver registry initialization concern (AC: #1, #4)\n  - [x] Option A implemented: validate only when `listDrivers().length > 0`, skip driver check if registry is empty\n  - [x] Parse can be called independently of engine startup without false positives\n\n- [x] Task 5: Write unit tests (AC: #8, #9)\n  - [x] Test: workflow with `driver: claude-code` and registered driver passes validation\n  - [x] Test: workflow with `driver: nonexistent` throws `WorkflowParseError` with driver name, task name, and registered drivers\n  - [x] Test: workflow with `agent: dev` (valid embedded agent) passes validation\n  - [x] Test: workflow with `agent: nonexistent-agent` throws `WorkflowParseError` with agent name, task name, and available agents\n  - [x] Test: workflow with multiple invalid refs collects all errors in one throw\n  - [x] Test: workflow with no `driver` field on any task passes (optional field)\n  - [x] Test: existing flow-ref checks still work (regression guard)\n  - [x] Test: backward compatibility — existing test workflows parse without errors\n  - [x] 12 new tests added, all passing. 4350 total tests pass."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":252,"cache_read_input_tokens":62434,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":252,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":73,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01K9WPLAQDFLLNWtkamPogoK","session_id":"4b1f7711-6ed7-4488-a0af-b261e761b450","uuid":"3793ec5a-7393-4384-ad48-c5c0171270ab"}
