{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01K9WPLAQDFLLNWtkamPogoK","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n## Summary\n\nImplemented story 11-2 (Workflow Referential Integrity Validation) across 3 files:\n\n**Files modified:**\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/agent-resolver.ts` — Added `listEmbeddedAgents()` export that reads `templates/agents/` and returns sorted agent names\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/workflow-parser.ts` — Added `validateReferentialIntegrity()` function and integrated it into `validateAndResolve()`. Validates driver refs against the driver registry (skipped when empty) and agent refs via `resolveAgent()`. All errors (dangling flow refs + driver/agent refs) collected and thrown in a single `WorkflowParseError`\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/workflow-parser.test.ts` — Added 12 new tests covering all 9 ACs. Updated 8 existing tests for the unified error message format and valid agent names\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/11-2-workflow-referential-integrity-validation.md` — Status changed to `review`, all tasks marked complete\n\n**Results:** Build succeeds with zero TypeScript errors. 4350 tests pass, 0 failures.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **Existing tests used arbitrary agent names** (\"builder\", \"custom-agent\", \"deployer\", \"my-custom-builder\", etc.) that are not resolvable agents. Updated these to use real embedded agent names (dev, qa, architect). This is a behavioral change for those test scenarios — they now test with valid agents rather than arbitrary strings.\n- **Error message wording changed** from \"Dangling task references:\" to \"Referential integrity errors:\" since all error types now flow through a unified path. 3 existing tests updated to match.\n- **No project-level agent validation test** — AC #6 says to accept agents resolvable via project/user-level overrides. The `resolveAgent()` call handles this, but no test creates a project-level agent override and verifies it passes. This would require writing a custom agent YAML to a temp dir and passing `cwd` through to `resolveAgent`, which the current `validateReferentialIntegrity` does not do (it calls `resolveAgent` without `cwd`). This is a gap — project-level custom agents won't be recognized by the validation at parse time unless they exist at the default `cwd`. Filed as a known limitation.\n- **`resolveAgent` called without `cwd`** in `validateReferentialIntegrity` — uses `process.cwd()` rather than the workflow's project directory. For `parseWorkflow(filePath)` calls, there's no project context available. For `resolveWorkflow({ cwd })`, the cwd is not passed through to the integrity check. This means project-level custom agents may not be found during validation if `cwd` differs from `process.cwd()`.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 18\n- By tool: Bash: 6, Read: 6, Edit: 11, Grep: 1, Write: 0, Skill: 0\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): test run with failures (~40 lines), full build+test (~20 lines), final build+test (~8 lines)\n- Files read: 6 unique, 8 total reads (workflow-parser.test.ts read 3 times across offset ranges)\n- Redundant operations: none significant — the 3 reads of workflow-parser.test.ts were necessary due to file size limits requiring offset-based reads"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a0b2008230dc18349 (use SendMessage with to: 'a0b2008230dc18349' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 66043\ntool_uses: 39\nduration_ms: 367148</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4b1f7711-6ed7-4488-a0af-b261e761b450","uuid":"72e4d2fe-df94-4871-8dea-a27f9693291d","timestamp":"2026-04-03T08:36:10.196Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-dev-story for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/11-2-workflow-referential-integrity-validation.md — implement all tasks, write tests, and 