{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011zqYPUya8mHRYL4djFbndv","type":"tool_result","content":"370\t## 4. What Went Well\n371\t\n372\t1. **Full lifecycle in one iteration.** Story 5-2 went from backlog to verified in a single 27-minute ralph iteration. This is the fastest full-lifecycle story completion yet.\n373\t2. **All phases passed on first attempt.** No retries, no stuck phases, no timeouts. The pipeline ran clean.\n374\t3. **Code review caught 3 HIGH bugs.** The stale verdict bug would have caused incorrect loop behavior in production. The 80-line duplication was a significant maintenance risk. Code review continues to earn its keep.\n375\t4. **High coverage.** 96.37% statement, 88.75% branch, 100% function coverage on the primary module. 27 new tests added.\n376\t5. **Budget adherence.** Completed in 27 minutes within a 30-minute timeout window. No timeout, no waste.\n377\t6. **Sprint velocity.** With 17/28 stories done (60.7%), the project is past the halfway mark. Epic 5 is at 50% (2/4).\n378\t\n379\t---\n380\t\n381\t## 5. What Went Wrong\n382\t\n383\t1. **Session issues log is non-functional.** `.session-issues.md` was not updated by any subagent this session. It still contains placeholder data from 2026-03-18. Without subagent self-reporting, cost analysis and issue tracking rely entirely on log file archaeology.\n384\t2. **`ralph/.state-snapshot.json` is increasingly stale.** Shows `sprint.done: 12` vs actual 17. Epic 5 `storiesDone: 0` despite 2 stories completed. The snapshot update mechanism is broken or not running after story completion.\n385\t3. **`codeharness stats` still broken.** Third consecutive session where cost reporting is unavailable. No `session-logs/` directory exists for ralph-driven sessions.\n386\t4. **Sprint-status.yaml was overwritten.** The parent orchestrator rewrote the entire sprint-status.yaml file (see live log line 4229). While the content was correct, the approach is fragile — it replaced a stale \"Epic Infinity\" placeholder that existed from an earlier bug, which means the file was corrupted at some point.\n387\t\n388\t---\n389\t\n390\t## 6. Lessons Learned\n391\t\n392\t### Patterns to Repeat\n393\t\n394\t- **Single-story-per-iteration pipeline.** The create → dev → review → verify pipeline completing in one iteration is the ideal execution pattern. No context switching, no state management between iterations.\n395\t- **Code review on loop/retry logic.** The stale verdict bug is exactly the kind of state-mutation bug that only appears under iteration. Always review loops and retry logic adversarially.\n396\t- **Building on prior story foundations.** Story 5-2 built directly on 5-1's sequential execution, reusing the same dispatch/checkpoint/error-handling patterns. Incremental stories within an epic pay off in velocity.\n397\t\n398\t### Patterns to Avoid\n399\t\n400\t- **Duplicating dispatch logic.** The 80-line duplication caught in review shows that when loop blocks share behavior with sequential steps, the code should be extracted into shared helpers from the start. The dev phase should anticipate this.\n401\t- **Relying on `.session-issues.md` for ralph sessions.** The file is not being written to. Either fix the mechanism or remove it from the retro requirements.\n402\t- **Trusting `ralph/.state-snapshot.json` as a source of truth.** It lags behind `sprint-status.yaml` and `sprint-state.json`. Use sprint-status.yaml for authoritative state.\n403\t\n404\t---\n405\t\n406\t## 7. Action Items\n407\t\n408\t| # | Action | Priority | Owner | Status |\n409\t|---|--------|----------|-------|--------|\n410\t| 1 | ~~Complete code-review and verify for story 5-1~~ | ~~HIGH~~ | ~~Session 2~~ | DONE |\n411\t| 2 | Fix `codeharness verify` to work without pre-set harness state flags | MEDIUM | Backlog | Open |\n412\t| 3 | Update `src/lib/AGENTS.md` — still missing: agent-dispatch, agent-resolver, session-manager, trace-id | MEDIUM | Next session | Partial |\n413\t| 4 | Fix `codeharness stats --save` to work for non-ralph sessions | MEDIUM | Backlog | Open (escalated from LOW — 3 sessions broken) |\n414\t| 5 | Fix `ralph/.state-snapshot.json` sync — shows 12 done vs 17 actual, Epic 5 storiesDone: 0 | MEDIUM | Next session | Open (escalated — divergence growing) |\n415\t| 6 | Fix `.session-issues.md` write mechanism for ralph-driven sessions | MEDIUM | Backlog | New |\n416\t| 7 | Fix pre-existing TS errors in `src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts` | LOW | Backlog | Open |\n417\t| 8 | Address deferred LOW issues from 4-3, 4-4, 5-1, and 5-2 code reviews | LOW | Backlog | Open (updated) |\n418\t| 9 | Add integration test for actual YAML parsing (not mocked) in workflow-engine | LOW | Backlog | Open |\n419\t| 10 | Extract shared dispatch/checkpoint logic from sequential and loop paths to eliminate duplication pattern | LOW | Next story touching workflow-engine | New |\n420\t\n421\t---\n422\t\n423\t# Session Retrospective — 2026-04-03 (Session 4)\n424\t\n425\t**Timestamp:** 2026-04-03T03:35Z\n426\t**Session window:** ~2026-04-03T02:41 to ~2026-04-03T03:34 (approx. 53 minutes)\n427\t**Sprint progress:** 20/28 stories done (71.4%), Epics 1-5 complete\n428\t\n429\t---\n430\t\n431\t## 1. Session Summary\n432\t\n433\tThis session completed Epic 5 — the final two stories (5-3 and 5-4) were implemented, reviewed, verified, and committed. Story 5-4 required two ralph iterations due to a timeout on iteration #9.\n434\t\n435\t| Story | Ralph Iteration | Phases Run | Outcome | Wall Time | Notes |\n436\t|-------|----------------|-----------|---------|-----------|-------|\n437\t| 5-3-crash-recovery-resume | #9 (partial) + commit in #9 output | create-story, dev-story, code-review, verify | **Done** | ~29 min | Completed within iteration #9 but iteration timed out at 30m during 5-4 work. Commit `8a89164`. |\n438\t| 5-4-run-status-commands | #9 (timeout) + #10 | create-story, dev-story, code-review, verify | **Done** | ~22 min (iter 10) | Iteration #9 timed out. Iteration #10 completed full lifecycle. Commit `3a27dad`. |\n439\t| Epic 5 milestone | — | — | **Done** | — | All 4 stories shipped. Commit `f4feb28`. |\n440\t\n441\t**Net output:** 2 stories completed + verified, 1 epic closed, sprint at 71.4%.\n442\t\n443\t---\n444\t\n445\t## 2. Issues Analysis\n446\t\n447\t### Bugs Found by Code Review (fixed)\n448\t\n449\t| Severity | Story | Issue |\n450\t|----------|-------|-------|\n451\t| HIGH | 5-4 | `--resume` flag registered but never read — `options.resume` ignored, engine's `phase === 'completed'` early-exit was never bypassed |\n452\t| MEDIUM | 5-4 | Story File List incomplete (missing `run-helpers.ts` dependency) |\n453\t\n454\tOnly 1 HIGH bug this session (down from 3 in Session 1 and 2 in Session 2). The `--resume` flag bug is a functional gap — the flag was wired in CLI but its value never reached the engine. Would have been a user-visible bug.\n455\t\n456\t### MEDIUM Issues (not fixed — tech debt)\n457\t\n458\t| Severity | Story | Issue |\n459\t|----------|-------|-------|\n460\t| MEDIUM | 5-4 | `formatElapsed` duplicated in 3 files with 3 different implementations |\n461\t| MEDIUM | 5-4 | 5 CLI options (`--timeout`, `--iteration-timeout`, `--calls`, `--max-story-retries`, `--reset`) parsed but never passed to EngineConfig. Pre-existing tech debt. |\n462\t| LOW | 5-4 | `run.ts` at 172 lines exceeds aspirational \"under 100\" guidance (within NFR9 300-line limit) |\n463\t| LOW | 5-4 | `formatElapsed` exported but only used internally in `formatters.ts` |\n464\t\n465\t### Infrastructure Issues\n466\t\n467\t- **Iteration #9 timed out at 30 minutes.** Story 5-3 was committed within iteration #9 but the iteration also started 5-4 work and ran out of time. The timeout report was saved (`ralph/logs/timeout-report-9-unknown.md`).\n468\t- **`.session-issues.md` was updated this session.** The write mechanism is functional again for iterations #9-10 (was broken in Session 3). The session issues log contains meaningful data for the 5-4 story.\n469\t- **`ralph/.state-snapshot.json` still divergent.** Shows `sprint.done: 13`, Epic 5 `storiesDone: 0` despite all 4 stories complete. The snapshot update mechanism continues to lag — now 7 stories behind reality (13 vs 20).\n470\t- **Config path mismatch:** `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml` referenced by create-story but doesn't exist; actual config at `_bmad/config.yaml`.\n471\t\n472\t### Verification Gaps\n473\t\n474\t- No session-issues entries were written for story 5-3. The create-story and dev-story phases for 5-3 completed without self-reporting — only 5-4 phases wrote to the log.\n475\t\n476\t---\n477\t\n478\t## 3. Cost Analysis\n479\t\n480\t### Iteration-Level Metrics\n481\t\n482\t| Ralph Iteration | Story Work | Log File Size | Wall Time | Outcome |\n483\t|-----------------|-----------|---------------|-----------|---------|\n484\t| #9 | 5-3 full + 5-4 partial | 2.15 MB | 30 min (timeout) | 5-3 committed, 5-4 timed out |\n485\t| #10 | 5-4 full | 2.67 MB | ~22 min | Completed |\n486\t| **Total** | | **4.82 MB** | **~53 min** | |\n487\t\n488\t### Subagent Token Report (from .session-issues.md — 5-4 only)\n489\t\n490\t| Subagent Phase | Tool Calls | Top Tools |\n491\t|---------------|------------|-----------|\n492\t| 5-4 create-story | 21 | Read: 14, Glob: 6, Write: 1, Skill: 1 |\n493\t| 5-4 dev-story | 24 | Read: 10, Bash: 8, Edit: 7, Write: 2, Grep: 2, Glob: 1 |\n494\t| 5-4 code-review | 22 | Read: 9, Bash: 7, Edit: 7, Grep: 2, Glob: 1, Skill: 1 |\n495\t| **5-4 Total** | **67** | Read: 33, Bash: 15, Edit: 14, Glob: 7, Grep: 4, Write: 3, Skill: 2 |\n496\t\n497\tStory 5-3 did not report to `.session-issues.md`. Estimated at ~60-70 tool calls based on log file size and prior story patterns.\n498\t\n499\t### Observations\n500\t\n501\t- **Read dominates** at 33/67 calls (49%) for 5-4. The create-story phase alone read 14 files — consistent with prior sessions where story creation is the most Read-heavy phase.\n502\t- **No redundant operations reported** in dev-story or code-review for 5-4. This is an improvement over Sessions 1-3 which each had 2-4 redundant operations.\n503\t- **Largest Bash outputs:** `npx vitest run` full suite (~30 lines), targeted tests (~28 lines), `ls` (~26 lines), `git diff` (~100 lines for code review).\n504\t- **Timeout waste:** Iteration #9 consumed 30 full minutes and a 2.15 MB log. Story 5-3 was committed but 5-4's partial work was lost and had to be redone in iteration #10. Estimated wasted cost: ~$2-3 (the 5-4 partial work).\n505\t\n506\t### Estimated Session Cost\n507\t\n508\t| Component | Estimated Cost |\n509\t|-----------|---------------|\n510\t| Story 5-3 (full lifecycle) | ~$4.50 |\n511\t| Story 5-4 — iteration #9 partial (wasted) | ~$2.50 |\n512\t| Story 5-4 — iteration #10 (full lifecycle) | ~$5.00 |\n513\t| Orchestrator overhead + retro | ~$1.50 |\n514\t| **Session total** | **~$13.50** |\n515\t\n516\t### Cumulative Cost Tracking\n517\t\n518\t| Session | Stories Completed | Estimated Cost | Cost/Story |\n519\t|---------|-------------------|---------------|------------|\n520\t| Prior sessions (Epics 1-2) | 7 | $37.08 | $4.45 |\n521\t| Session 1 (2026-04-03, early) | 2.5 | ~$12.00 | ~$4.80 |\n522\t| Session 2 (2026-04-03, late) | 0.5 | ~$3.50 | ~$7.00* |\n523\t| Session 3 | 1 | ~$4.50 | ~$4.50 |\n524\t| **Session 4 (this)** | **2** | **~$13.50** | **~$6.75** |\n525\t| **Cumulative** | **13** | **~$70.58** | **~$5.43** |\n526\t\n527\t*Session 2 and this session's per-story cost are inflated by waste (Session 2: tail-end work; Session 4: timeout retry).\n528\t\n529\t### Cost Optimization Opportunities\n530\t\n531\t1. **Timeout budget:** Iteration #9 tried to do two stories (5-3 + 5-4) and timed out. If the orchestrator had committed after 5-3 and started a new iteration for 5-4, the ~$2.50 partial work would not have been lost.\n532\t2. **5 dead CLI options:** The 5 parsed-but-unused CLI flags (`--timeout`, `--iteration-timeout`, `--calls`, `--max-story-retries`, `--reset`) represent wasted complexity in every code review that has to assess them.\n533\t3. **`formatElapsed` x3:** Three implementations of the same function across the codebase. Each code review flags it but defers. The accumulated review cost of re-evaluating this each time likely exceeds the fix cost.\n534\t\n535\t---\n536\t\n537\t## 4. What Went Well\n538\t\n539\t1. **Epic 5 completed.** All 4 stories (sequential steps, loop blocks, crash recovery, run/status commands) are done. The workflow engine is now fully functional.\n540\t2. **Recovery from timeout.** Iteration #9 timed out but iteration #10 completed 5-4 cleanly in ~22 minutes. The retry mechanism works.\n541\t3. **Session issues log functional again.** After being broken in Session 3, the `.session-issues.md` mechanism worked for Session 4's iteration #10. This produced usable token reports for the retrospective.\n542\t4. **Code review quality maintained.** Found the `--resume` flag bug — a flag that was advertised in CLI help but silently did nothing. This would have been confusing for users.\n543\t5. **Sprint velocity at 71.4%.** 20/28 stories done. The remaining 8 stories span Epics 6-9 (evaluator, circuit breaker, issue tracker, workflow patches).\n544\t6. **Zero story retries.** Both 5-3 and 5-4 completed on first attempt (the timeout was an iteration timeout, not a story retry). No stuck cycles.\n545\t7. **Coverage remains high.** 96.78% overall, all 158 files above 80% floor.\n546\t\n547\t---\n548\t\n549\t## 5. What Went Wrong\n550\t\n551\t1. **Iteration #9 timeout.** Attempted to complete both 5-3 and 5-4 in a single 30-minute iteration. 5-3 committed successfully but the remaining time was insufficient for 5-4. Wasted ~$2.50 in partial work.\n552\t2. **No session issues for story 5-3.** The create-story and dev-story phases for 5-3 did not write to `.session-issues.md`, making cost analysis and issue tracking incomplete for half this session.\n553\t3. **`ralph/.state-snapshot.json` is now 7 stories behind.** Shows 13 done vs 20 actual. Epic 5 shows `storiesDone: 0`. This file is increasingly useless as a state reference.\n554\t4. **`formatElapsed` duplication flagged for the 4th time.** This tech debt item keeps getting deferred. It's now been flagged in Sessions 1, 2, 3, and 4 code reviews.\n555\t5. **5 dead CLI options still present.** Pre-existing tech debt that every code review has to evaluate and then skip. Each review cycle burns ~2-3 minutes on this.\n556\t\n557\t---\n558\t\n559\t## 6. Lessons Learned\n560\t\n561\t### Patterns to Repeat\n562\t\n563\t- **One story per iteration.** Iterations that complete one story cleanly (like #8 for 5-2 and #10 for 5-4) have 100% success rate. Iteration #9 tried to squeeze in two and timed out.\n564\t- **Code review catches wiring bugs.** The `--resume` flag bug is the kind of \"plumbing\" error that tests don't catch because tests typically test the engine directly, not the CLI→engine wiring.\n565\t- **Session issues log when it works.** The 5-4 token reports enabled precise cost analysis. When the mechanism works, it's valuable.\n566\t\n567\t### Patterns to Avoid\n568\t\n569\t- **Two stories in one iteration.** The 30-minute budget is tight for a full lifecycle (create → dev → review → verify). Attempting two stories risks timeout and wasted partial work."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_017khBip83pX1he8i2ZXQoeU","session_id":"4b1f7711-6ed7-4488-a0af-b261e761b450","uuid":"5e018b19-d4c2-44f2-b5fc-a7321aca8ea7","timestamp":"2026-04-03T08:45:32.049Z"}
