| Backlog | Open |\n589\t| 11 | **Fix `formatElapsed` duplication** — 3 implementations across codebase, flagged 4 sessions in a row | MEDIUM | Next sprint | New (escalated from LOW) |\n590\t| 12 | **Wire 5 dead CLI options** (`--timeout`, `--iteration-timeout`, `--calls`, `--max-story-retries`, `--reset`) to EngineConfig or remove them | MEDIUM | Next sprint | New (escalated from LOW) |\n591\t| 13 | **Limit ralph to 1 story per iteration** to prevent timeout waste | LOW | Backlog | New |\n592\t\n593\t---\n594\t\n595\t# Session Retrospective — 2026-04-03 (Session 5)\n596\t\n597\t**Timestamp:** 2026-04-03T04:00Z\n598\t**Session window:** ~2026-04-03T03:11 to ~2026-04-03T03:55 (approx. 44 minutes)\n599\t**Sprint progress:** 21/28 stories done (75%), Epics 1-5 complete, Epic 6 at 1/3\n600\t\n601\t---\n602\t\n603\t## 1. Session Summary\n604\t\n605\tThis session covered ralph iterations #11 and #12. Iteration #11 completed stories 5-3, 5-4, and the Epic 5 milestone (these were the tail-end commit/verify work from Session 4). Iteration #12 completed story 6-1, the first story of Epic 6 (Blind Evaluator & Verification).\n606\t\n607\t| Story | Ralph Iteration | Phases Run | Outcome | Notes |\n608\t|-------|----------------|-----------|---------|-------|\n609\t| 5-3-crash-recovery-resume | #11 (commit tail) | — | **Done** (already done in Session 4) | Commit `8a89164` |\n610\t| 5-4-run-status-commands | #11 (commit tail) | — | **Done** (already done in Session 4) | Commit `3a27dad` |\n611\t| Epic 5 milestone | #11 | — | **Done** | Commit `f4feb28` |\n612\t| 6-1-evaluator-module-workspace-spawn | #12 | create-story, dev-story, code-review, verification | **Done** | Full lifecycle. Commit `fb76b15`. |\n613\t\n614\t**Net new output this session:** 1 story completed end-to-end (6-1), 1 epic milestone committed (Epic 5).\n615\t\n616\t---\n617\t\n618\t## 2. Issues Analysis\n619\t\n620\t### Bugs Found by Code Review (fixed)\n621\t\n622\t| Severity | Story | Issue |\n623\t|----------|-------|-------|\n624\t| HIGH | 6-1 | Timer leak — `setTimeout` in `Promise.race` never cleared on success path. Could keep Node.js alive 5 min after evaluator completes. |\n625\t| MEDIUM | 6-1 | Non-Error rejection path untested. Test added. |\n626\t| MEDIUM | 6-1 | Workspace creation failure path untested. Test added. |\n627\t\n628\tThe timer leak is a real resource issue. In long-running CLI sessions, leaked timers accumulate and prevent clean process exit. This was caught by code review and fixed with `clearTimeout` on the success path.\n629\t\n630\t### LOW Issues (not fixed — tech debt)\n631\t\n632\t| Severity | Story | Issue |\n633\t|----------|-------|-------|\n634\t| LOW | 6-1 | `buildUnknownOutput` names findings `ac: index + 1` mapping to story files, not actual ACs. Misleading naming — downstream parsing (story 6-2) will handle. |\n635\t| LOW | 6-1 | `isDockerAvailable()` is synchronous `execFileSync` blocking event loop up to 10s. Acceptable for CLI. |\n636\t\n637\t### Risks Identified During Story Creation\n638\t\n639\t- **Epic naming collision:** `epic-6-retrospective.md` documents a previous sprint's Epic 6 (Dashboard Visualization Rework), not the current Epic 6 (Blind Evaluator & Verification). Subagent navigated past it but this is a source of confusion.\n640\t- **Timeout via `Promise.race()` does not abort the underlying SDK session.** Agent may continue running after timeout. Known architectural trade-off — no clean abort mechanism exists for the Claude SDK.\n641\t- **`EvaluatorVerdict` type duplication risk.** Already defined in `workflow-engine.ts` (story 5-2). Story 6-1's `EvaluatorResult` returns raw `output: string` — consolidation deferred to story 6-2.\n642\t\n643\t### Verification Gaps\n644\t\n645\t- **AGENTS.md stale:** `codeharness verify` flagged `AGENTS.md` missing `evaluator.ts` from module listing. Documentation artifact issue, not an AC failure.\n646\t- **AC 3 partial reliance on pre-compiled agent definition:** Evaluator receives `bare: true` and `source_access: false` but doesn't set them. By design — the agent definition is pre-compiled.\n647\t- **Branch coverage 92.85%:** Uncovered branch at line 160 is a defensive `if (timeoutTimer)` guard. Timer is always set so the false branch is unreachable in practice.\n648\t\n649\t### Infrastructure Issues\n650\t\n651\t- **`ralph/.state-snapshot.json` still divergent.** Now shows `sprint.done: 13` (from Session 3 era) vs actual 21 done. Gap has grown to 8 stories.\n652\t- **Vitest run twice during verification:** Full coverage run + evaluator-only run. Could have been combined into a single run.\n653\t- **Config path mismatch persists:** `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml` referenced but doesn't exist; actual config at `_bmad/config.yaml`.\n654\t\n655\t---\n656\t\n657\t## 3. Cost Analysis\n658\t\n659\t### Iteration-Level Metrics\n660\t\n661\t| Ralph Iteration | Story Work | Log File Size | Wall Time (approx) | Outcome |\n662\t|-----------------|-----------|---------------|---------------------|---------|\n663\t| #11 | Epic 5 milestone commit, 6-1 story creation start | 2.75 MB | ~26 min | Completed |\n664\t| #12 | 6-1 full lifecycle | 2.32 MB | ~17 min | Completed |\n665\t| **Total** | | **5.07 MB** | **~44 min** | |\n666\t\n667\t### Subagent Token Report (from .session-issues.md)\n668\t\n669\t| Subagent Phase | Tool Calls | Read | Bash | Edit | Grep | Glob | Write | Skill |\n670\t|---------------|------------|------|------|------|------|------|-------|-------|\n671\t| 6-1 create-story | 16 | 8 | 0 | 0 | 1 | 7 | 1 | 0 |\n672\t| 6-1 dev-story | 14 | 7 | 6 | 2 | 1 | 0 | 2 | 0 |\n673\t| 6-1 code-review | 18 | 8 | 7 | 3 | 1 | 1 | 0 | 1 |\n674\t| 6-1 verification | 14 | 2 | 8 | 0 | 4 | 0 | 1 | 0 |\n675\t| **6-1 Total** | **62** | **25** | **21** | **5** | **7** | **8** | **4** | **1** |\n676\t\n677\tAlso includes 5-4 subagent reports from iteration #11 (carried over from Session 4):\n678\t\n679\t| Subagent Phase | Tool Calls | Read | Bash | Edit | Grep | Glob | Write | Skill |\n680\t|---------------|------------|------|------|------|------|------|-------|-------|\n681\t| 5-4 create-story | 21 | 14 | 2 | 0 | 1 | 6 | 1 | 1 |\n682\t| 5-4 dev-story | 24 | 10 | 8 | 7 | 2 | 1 | 2 | 0 |\n683\t| 5-4 code-review | 22 | 9 | 7 | 7 | 2 | 1 | 0 | 1 |\n684\t| **5-4 Total** | **67** | **33** | **17** | **14** | **5** | **8** | **3** | **2** |\n685\t\n686\t### Subagent-Level Breakdown — Where Tokens Were Spent\n687\t\n688\t**Most tool-call-heavy phases:**\n689\t1. 5-4 dev-story (24 calls) and 5-4 code-review (22 calls) — consistent with prior sessions where dev and review are the most expensive phases.\n690\t2. 6-1 code-review (18 calls) — lower than 5-4 because evaluator.ts is a smaller, more focused module.\n691\t\n692\t**Redundant operations identified:**\n693\t- 6-1 verification: vitest ran twice (full suite + evaluator-only). Could have been a single targeted run with `--coverage`.\n694\t- 5-4 create-story: one redundant read of `sprint-status.yaml`.\n695\t- No file was read 3+ times in any subagent phase — an improvement over earlier sessions.\n696\t\n697\t**Largest Bash outputs:**\n698\t- `npx tsc --noEmit` (~130 lines) in 6-1 dev-story — TypeScript check is verbose\n699\t- `npx vitest --coverage` (~140 lines) in 6-1 dev-story\n700\t- `ls verification/` (~133 lines) in 6-1 verification — large directory listing\n701\t- `git diff HEAD -- src/commands/run.ts` (~100 lines) in 5-4 code-review\n702\t\n703\t**Read-heaviness:** 25/62 calls (40%) for 6-1 were Read. 33/67 (49%) for 5-4. Story creation is consistently the most Read-heavy phase (8/16 = 50% for 6-1 create-story, 14/21 = 67% for 5-4 create-story).\n704\t\n705\t### Estimated Session Cost\n706\t\n707\t| Component | Estimated Cost |\n708\t|-----------|---------------|\n709\t| Story 6-1 (full lifecycle, 62 tool calls) | ~$5.00 |\n710\t| Iteration #11 overhead (Epic 5 commit, orchestrator) | ~$1.50 |\n711\t| Orchestrator + retro overhead | ~$1.00 |\n712\t| **Session total** | **~$7.50** |\n713\t\n714\t### Cumulative Cost Tracking\n715\t\n716\t| Session | Stories Completed | Estimated Cost | Cost/Story |\n717\t|---------|-------------------|---------------|------------|\n718\t| Prior sessions (Epics 1-2) | 7 | $37.08 | $4.45 |\n719\t| Session 1 (2026-04-03, early) | 2.5 | ~$12.00 | ~$4.80 |\n720\t| Session 2 (2026-04-03, late) | 0.5 | ~$3.50 | ~$7.00* |\n721\t| Session 3 | 1 | ~$4.50 | ~$4.50 |\n722\t| Session 4 | 2 | ~$13.50 | ~$6.75 |\n723\t| **Session 5 (this)** | **1** | **~$7.50** | **~$7.50** |\n724\t| **Cumulative** | **14** | **~$78.08** | **~$5.58** |\n725\t\n726\t*Session 5 cost/story is higher than average because iteration #11 spent time on Epic 5 milestone commit work (not a new story) and the orchestrator overhead was spread across only 1 new story.\n727\t\n728\t### Wasted Spend\n729\t\n730\t- **Duplicate vitest runs in verification:** ~$0.50 wasted. Verification ran vitest twice — once full suite, once evaluator-only.\n731\t- **Iteration #11 overhead:** ~$1.50 spent on committing already-done work from Session 4 and orchestrating the transition to Epic 6.\n732\t- **Total estimated waste this session:** ~$2.00 (27% of session cost)\n733\t\n734\t### Cost Optimization Opportunities\n735\t\n736\t1. **Combine vitest runs in verification phase.** A single `npx vitest run --coverage` with the right filter produces both test results and coverage. Running it twice is pure waste.\n737\t2. **Reduce `ls` output in verification.** The 133-line directory listing of `verification/` is mostly noise. Verification should target specific files, not browse directories.\n738\t3. **Story creation Read count.** 6-1 create-story read 10 unique files. Consider pre-loading a \"story context bundle\" that combines architecture, PRD, and epic summary into a single reference document.\n739\t\n740\t---\n741\t\n742\t## 4. What Went Well\n743\t\n744\t1. **Story 6-1 completed in one clean iteration.** Full lifecycle (create, dev, review, verify) in ~17 minutes. This is the fastest story completion yet, beating 5-2's 27-minute record.\n745\t2. **Code review caught a real timer leak.** The `setTimeout` leak in `Promise.race` is exactly the kind of resource bug that causes mysterious CI hangs and slow exits. Fixed before merge.\n746\t3. **Zero redundant file reads.** No file was read 3+ times in any subagent phase. This is the first session with no file-read redundancy.\n747\t4. **Session issues log fully functional.** All 4 phases of 6-1 wrote token reports. This is the first session where every phase reported.\n748\t5. **Sprint at 75%.** 21/28 stories done. Epic 6 is underway with 1/3 stories complete.\n749\t6. **Circuit breaker stable.** CLOSED state, 0 total opens, 0 consecutive failures. The system is running healthy.\n750\t7. **Coverage remains high.** 96.79% overall. Evaluator module at 100/92.85/100/100 (stmt/branch/func/line).\n751\t\n752\t---\n753\t\n754\t## 5. What Went Wrong\n755\t\n756\t1. **`ralph/.state-snapshot.json` now 8 stories behind reality.** Shows 13 done vs 21 actual. This file is actively misleading and should either be fixed or deleted.\n757\t2. **`codeharness stats` still broken.** Fifth consecutive session. The cost report mechanism has been non-functional since Session 1. All cost analysis in this and prior retros is manual estimation.\n758\t3. **AGENTS.md still stale.** Now missing `evaluator.ts` in addition to `agent-dispatch.ts`, `agent-resolver.ts`, `session-manager.ts`, `trace-id.ts`. 5 modules behind (was 4 in Session 4 — growing).\n759\t4. **Epic naming collision.** `epic-6-retrospective.md` refers to an old Epic 6 (Dashboard Visualization Rework), not the current one (Blind Evaluator & Verification). Creates confusion for subagents navigating the file tree.\n760\t5. **Verification ran vitest twice.** Known redundancy pattern that keeps recurring. Verification subagent is not learning from prior session lessons.\n761\t6. **`EvaluatorVerdict` type exists in two conceptual locations.** `workflow-engine.ts` has it from story 5-2, and story 6-1 introduces `EvaluatorResult` with different semantics. This needs consolidation in story 6-2 or it will cause confusion.\n762\t\n763\t---\n764\t\n765\t## 6. Lessons Learned\n766\t\n767\t### Patterns to Repeat\n768\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_017khBip83pX1he8i2ZXQoeU","session_id":"4b1f7711-6ed7-4488-a0af-b261e761b450","uuid":"3876ecec-a6b7-4435-ae38-46e698dd76dd","timestamp":"2026-04-03T08:45:35.979Z"}
